text:
Hi, I can not load mod_proxy_connect at startup . I have compiled from source .
I'm running two instances with the same binaries. Instance listening in port 80
works  fine. When I try to start the instance in port 443 with SSL it raises
this error:

httpd: Syntax error on line 11 of /app/proxy_ssl/etc/httpd.conf: Cannot load
/app/base/apache/httpd/modules/mod_proxy_connect.so into server: ld.so.1: httpd:
fatal: relocation error: file
/app/base/apache/httpd/modules/mod_proxy_connect.so: symbol
ap_get_server_banner: referenced symbol not found


Modules are loaded in the same order in both instances.
creator: asantiago@atlasit.com
